---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About Ismail El Jamiy — PhD candidate in AI, engineer, and photographer from Morocco, based in Toulouse.">

  <article class="page-container">

    <header class="page-header">
      <h1 class="page-title">About</h1>
      <div class="page-rule" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">

      <p class="drop-cap">
        I'm a PhD candidate in Artificial Intelligence at the University of Toulouse
        (IRIT / IMT / CLLE), working on the automatic recognition of handwritten text
        in medieval Arabic scientific manuscripts. My research sits at a rare intersection:
        modern deep learning applied to a heritage that spans centuries of Islamic scholarship
        in mathematics, astronomy, and medicine.
      </p>

      <p>
        Before Toulouse, I trained as a State Engineer in AI and Computer Science at the
        École Nationale Supérieure d'Arts et Métiers in Casablanca — graduating with
        Highest Distinction in 2025. Those years shaped my instinct for rigorous engineering
        and gave me a grounding in both the theoretical and applied sides of machine learning.
      </p>

      <h2>Research</h2>
      <p>
        My PhD topic combines two challenges that individually push the state of the art:
        handwritten text recognition (HTR) in degraded historical documents, and the
        specificities of classical Arabic script — a cursive, context-dependent writing
        system with rich morphology. The manuscripts I work with are often centuries old,
        written by multiple hands, and held in collections across Morocco, Algeria, and
        Europe. Unlocking them computationally means making them searchable, citable,
        and accessible to researchers worldwide.
      </p>
      <p>
        Beyond recognition, I am interested in training dedicated language models on the
        recognised text — models that understand the vocabulary, grammar, and semantic
        patterns of medieval Arabic scientific prose. Think of it as building a specialised
        AI collaborator for historians of science.
      </p>

      <h2>Background</h2>
      <p>
        I grew up in Mohammedia, Morocco. Arabic is my mother tongue; French is a second
        language I have spoken since childhood (TCF C1, score 543). I moved to France in
        late 2025 for the PhD and now live in Toulouse. Before that, I completed internships
        in medical image segmentation at IRIT, computer vision for insurance claims at
        SYGMA.AI, and PPE detection for industrial safety at Lesieur Cristal.
      </p>

      <h2>Beyond the lab</h2>
      <p>
        I photograph. Not as a side hobby but as a genuine practice — I am drawn to
        street scenes, light at the edges of day, and the geometry of cities. I also
        follow football closely (tactical maps feel less abstract when you have watched
        enough matches), and I travel whenever the PhD budget allows.
      </p>

      <h2>Languages</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Arabic</strong> — Native</li>
        <li><strong>French</strong> — Bilingual (TCF C1, score 543)</li>
        <li><strong>English</strong> — Advanced</li>
      </ul>

    </div>

  </article>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 5rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .page-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .page-rule {
    height: 2px;
    background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-olive), transparent);
    border-radius: 1px;
  }

  /* ── Prose ────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .prose {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1.4em;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-olive);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .prose h2 {
    color: var(--color-gold);
  }

  .prose ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-bottom: 1.4em;
  }

  .prose ul li {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 0.4em;
  }

  .prose ul li::before {
    content: "—";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-terracotta);
  }

  /* Drop cap on first paragraph */
  .drop-cap::first-letter {
    font-size: 4.5em;
    line-height: 0.78;
    float: left;
    margin-right: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-terracotta);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
  }
</style>
